**Why:** Uniform sentence length creates a metronome effect that reads as monotone; variation creates emphasis and pace.
**When:** Blog posts, long-form emails, any writing meant to hold attention

**Before:** `We built the tool over six months. The team worked across three time zones. Every sprint taught us something new.`
**After:** `We built the tool over six months, working across three time zones. Every sprint taught us something new.`

